article.description: — Kimani Hamilton's 23 points helped High Point defeat Bellarmine 90-85 on Saturday night.
article.headline: High Point beats Bellarmine 90-85
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- — Kimani Hamilton's 23 points helped High Point defeat Bellarmine 90-85 on Saturday night. Hamilton had six rebounds and three steals for the Panthers (11-4). Duke Miles scored 16 points while going 6 of 12 from the floor, including 0 for 3 from 3-point range, and 4 for 5 from the line. Abdoulaye Thiam had 14 points and was 5 of 9 shooting (2 for 4 from 3-point range). The Knights (4-11) were led by Ben Johnson, who posted 32 points, seven rebounds and two steals. Peter Suder added 18 points, six rebounds and six assists for Bellarmine. In addition, Alec Pfriem had 15 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
